Describe a time you missed / forgot an appointment
- what the appointment was
- where and when it was
- why you forgot about it
- how you felt

I’d like to talk about a time when I missed an important appointment with my high school teacher, which is something I still regret.

This happened about two years ago during Tet, when students usually visit their former teachers to show respect and send New Year wishes. I had planned to visit my homeroom teacher, Mr. Huy, together with some of my classmates.

He was a very important person to me because he had always supported me, not only in my studies but also in my personal life. He even gave me advice on choosing my university major.

However, at that time, I was extremely busy preparing for an important exam after the holiday, so I decided to cancel the visit and asked my friends to send my regards instead. I thought I would have another chance to see him the following year.

Unfortunately, a few months later, he passed away after contracting COVID-19. I was completely shocked when I heard the news. It suddenly hit me that I had missed my last opportunity to see him in person.

I felt deeply regretful, and honestly, it’s something I still think about from time to time. This experience taught me an important lesson: we should always make time for the people we care about, because we never know when it might be the last chance.
